{
  "id": "10008",
  "key": "GG-5",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Establish Secure Connection to Jira Cloud REST API",
    "description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use case:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As a "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "member of Team Gamma",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "I want to establish a secure connection to the Jira Cloud REST API, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "so that we can fetch Jira issues, workflows, screens, and custom fields for migration."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Acceptance criteria:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "GIVEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the need to connect to Jira Cloud's REST API securely, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "WHEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " integrating with the Jira Cloud API, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AND",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " handling sensitive credentials such as API tokens or OAuth securely on the backend,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "THEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the connection must be established using secure encryption and without exposing any sensitive data in logs or version control."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Technical notes:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "It's crucial to use secure authentication mechanisms like API tokens or OAuth when connecting to the Jira Cloud REST API. This ensures that credentials are handled securely and never exposed. Additionally, we need to implement secure storage for collected credentials on the backend and utilize encryption for all sensitive data transmission. The use of HTTPS for communication is mandatory to ensure a secure connection between Team Gamma's backend and Jira Cloud's REST API."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
